The paper deals with the problem of finding the mixed domination number of a graph, which is a well-studied problem in the field of graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The algorithm presented in the paper is based on parse trees and is specifically designed for generalized series-parallel graphs, which are a well-known class of graphs with many interesting properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the problem of mixed domination has connections to graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely sub-categories.
